  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary font-label font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-1 rounded-full">{post.category}</span>
        <time class="font-body text-sm text-secondary">{post.date}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-headline text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tighter text-on-surface mb-4">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Shipping glassware, ceramics, porcelain, and other fragile items is risky. A single crack during transit ruins the sale and frustrates customers. Corrugated cardboard sheets are an underrated but highly effective protection solution, offering structural separation and impact absorption for delicate shipments across Peninsular Malaysia.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Why Corrugated Cardboard Dividers Protect Glassware</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Prevents Item-to-Item Contact</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">The primary cause of breakage is items touching and shifting during transport. Corrugated dividers create rigid separation between glassware, preventing collision and vibration damage. Each item is isolated in its own protective chamber.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Absorbs Impact & Vibration</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Corrugated flutes compress slightly under pressure, absorbing road vibrations and minor impacts. This energy dissipation reduces the force transmitted to delicate items, lowering breakage rates significantly.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Cost-Effective Compared to Alternatives</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Corrugated sheets cost RM 0.20–0.50 each versus RM 5–15 for foam inserts or specialty packaging. For high-volume glassware shipments, cardboard dividers reduce packaging costs while maintaining protection levels.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Recyclable & Eco-Friendly</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Customers appreciate sustainability. Corrugated cardboard is 100% recyclable and compostable — a better environmental choice than plastic or foam packaging.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Best Practices for Packing Glassware with Cardboard Dividers</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Layer Structure for Wine Glasses & Drinking Glasses</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">1. Wrap each glass stem in bubble wrap (2–3 layers). 2. Lay wrapped glasses on their side. 3. Place corrugated sheet between each row. 4. Stack no more than 3–4 rows per carton. 5. Fill base and gaps with packing peanuts or paper filler. 6. Seal carton with strong tape.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Plate & Dish Stacking Method</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Plates are best packed vertically (like records) rather than stacked flat, as flat stacking concentrates weight on single points. Use corrugated dividers between every plate or every 2–3 plates depending on thickness. Insert cardboard spacers to prevent sliding.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Ceramic Bowls & Curved Items</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Nest bowls with corrugated sheet dividers between layers. Reinforce bowl rims with extra bubble wrap since that's where stress concentrates during shifting. Use small boxes (avoid large, heavy boxes) to minimize weight and reduce crushing risk.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Vases & Tall Fragile Items</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Pack upright in tall cartons surrounded by corrugated dividers creating a snug fit. Wrap in bubble wrap to add cushioning. Use crinkle paper at the top to prevent shifting. Ensure carton is clearly labeled FRAGILE and THIS SIDE UP.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Combination Packing: Cardboard + Bubble Wrap</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">For maximum protection, combine methods: Bubble wrap around individual items + corrugated dividers between items + crinkle paper in gaps. This dual-layer approach reduces breakage to near-zero for most items.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-8">
        <h3 class="font-headline text-lg font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Corrugated Cardboard Types for Glassware Protection</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm font-body">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-bold">Type</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-bold">Best For</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-bold">Thickness</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 font-bold">Cost/Sheet</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Single-wall (A-flute)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Light glasses, minimal protection</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">4.5mm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">RM 0.20</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Single-wall (B-flute)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Standard glassware, good cushioning</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">3mm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">RM 0.25</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Double-wall (BC)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Heavy ceramics, dishes, premium items</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">7mm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">RM 0.50</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Wax-coated</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">Moisture-prone items, overseas shipping</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">3–7mm</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4">RM 0.50–0.80</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Real-World Example: Wine Glass Shipping</h2>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6"><strong>Scenario: A restaurant supplies shop ships 20 wine glasses via standard courier to Kuala Lumpur.</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Wrap each glass stem in 1 layer bubble wrap</li>
          <li>Place 10 wrapped glasses in carton on their side</li>
          <li>Insert corrugated sheet divider between each 2–3 glasses</li>
          <li>Fill gaps with crinkle paper (no peanuts that shift)</li>
          <li>Add corrugated sheet buffer at bottom and top of carton</li>
          <li>Cost: RM 2.50 bubble wrap + RM 0.75 cardboard dividers (4 sheets) = RM 3.25 total protection per shipment</li>
          <li>Result: 95%+ delivery success rate with zero breakage</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">FAQs on Corrugated Cardboard for Glassware</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface mb-3">How many corrugated sheets do I need per carton?</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Rule of thumb: 1 sheet per layer of items, plus 1–2 buffer sheets at box bottom/top. A carton with 10 glasses (5 layers) needs 6–7 sheets minimum.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface mb-3">Can I reuse corrugated dividers?</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Yes, they can be reused 2–3 times if undamaged. However, cost-wise, it's often not worth storing and cleaning sheets. Fresh sheets ensure reliability.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface mb-3">What's the minimum order for corrugated sheets?</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Quinocycle minimum order is RM 1,000. A standard 3mm corrugated sheet costs RM 0.25, so you'd receive roughly 4,000 sheets. Bulk pricing available for larger orders.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface mb-3">Do corrugated sheets protect better than foam?</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Foam provides more cushioning; cardboard provides structural separation. Ideal: combine both. For cost-conscious shipping, cardboard dividers + bubble wrap offers 90% of foam's protection at 40% of the cost.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface mb-3">Can sheets be custom-cut to fit my cartons?</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Yes. Quinocycle offers custom sheet cutting for large orders. Specify desired dimensions and order quantity. Custom cutting adds a small fee (RM 0.05–0.10 per sheet).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Source Your Corrugated Dividers from Quinocycle Balakong</h2>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Glassware, ceramics, and dishware retailers across Peninsular Malaysia trust Quinocycle for high-quality, affordable corrugated cardboard sheets. We stock standard B-flute and A-flute sheets, and can provide custom cuts for bulk orders. Minimum order RM 1,000; fast delivery to Balakong, Cheras, Kajang, KL, and throughout Selangor.</p>
        <div class="bg-primary text-on-primary rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
          <p class="font-body mb-4 font-semibold">Order Corrugated Dividers Today</p>
          <a href={WA_LINK} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-on-primary text-primary font-label font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-surface transition">📱 Chat on WhatsApp</a>
          <p class="font-body text-on-primary/80 text-sm mt-4">Phone: +60168916381 | Email: quinocycle@gmail.com</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">Corrugated cardboard sheets are a simple, cost-effective solution for protecting fragile glassware and ceramics during shipping. Combined with bubble wrap and proper packing technique, cardboard dividers reduce breakage rates and customer returns. Invest in quality protection and protect your reputation.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
